        <V n="text" t="single">
          <T n="single">0xA276B4BF<!--String: "The fossil evidence around Gibbi Point hints at varying sizes of Plumbird; it's as if they shrunk over time. Locals have noted that they were once largely located near what's known as Hothead Rock Geyser in Wanderwood Wilds. In fact, it's so named because the Plumbirds became aware that by tapping a certain boulder with their beaks, lava would explode and a unique butterfly could be found.\n\nThis butterfly is a super-scrumptious treat for the Plumbirds, who may have over-indulged to a point where lava explosions created crispy birds. Soon they began seeking other locales, finding themselves clustered often at Fletcher's Point in Jellyfish Junction. There they'd gather to watch the sealife (and perhaps gobble up fishy treats on their own) and astonish Sims passing by in boats."--></T>
        </V>
